SD.3 StructureDefinition-patient-mhr-1

My Health Record Patient [Draft]

SD.3.1 Formal Views of Profile Content

The official URL for this profile is: 

http://ns.electronichealth.net.au/ci/fhir/4.0/StructureDefinition/patient-mhr-1

The purpose of this profile is to define a representation of a patient in an electronic exchange with the My Health Record system of health information such as a discharge summary or medicines list.

Must Support

In the context of this profile Must Support SHALL be interpreted as follows:

  • The system SHALL be able to include the element when authoring a resource where data is available

  • The system SHALL be able to store and retrieve the element

  • The system SHALL be able to process resources containing the element

This profile builds on AUBasePatient.

This profile was published on Tue May 26 13:04:36 AEST 2020 as a draft by Australian Digital Health Agency.

SD.3.2 - Known Issues

Reference Description Issue No.
Profile URL The canonical URL for this profile may move to a version independent canonical URL pending design decisions around the support of additional elements. See ci-fhir-r4/issues/17
Patient (biological sex) FHIR Patient model allows for recording administrative gender for a patient. It does not allow recording sex for a patient. We have a requirement to record patient's biological sex (sex at birth) as well as gender. We are working on solutions for recording a patient's biological sex. See au-fhir-base/issues/321 See ci-fhir-r4/issues/15
Patient (year of arrival) We are working on supporting year of arrival in Australia as part of the minimum CALD (Cultural and Linguistic Diversity) data set in electronic health. See au-fhir-base/issues/357 See ci-fhir-r4/issues/13
contact (use cases) At this time the usage scenarios are undefined for exchanging a patient's contact information with the My Health Record system. See ci-fhir-r4/issues/16
contact.relationship (terminology) Work is underway to bind to terminology supporting contact relationship types in an Australian healthcare context. This work is expected to result in support for values from Contact Relationship Type See ci-fhir-r4/issues/16
generalPractitioner (PractitionerRole) PractitionerRole profiles are not yet available. See ci-fhir-r4/issues/7
